OL,7,FBRUSSELS ` The European Central Bank on
OL,8,FThursday raised interest rates by half
OL,9,Fa percentage point to 3 per cent, while
OL,10,Finsisting it was "monitoring current
OL,11,Fmarket tensions closely" in the wake of
OL,12,Fthe collapse of Credit Suisse shares.
OL,14,FSpeaking in Frankfurt, ECB President
OL,15,FChristine Lagarde said the rate hike
OL,16,Freflected the prioritisation of the
OL,17,Fcontinued fight against inflation over
OL,18,Ffinancial stability concerns, noting
OL,19,Fthat "inflation is projected to remain
OL,20,Ftoo high for too long".
OL,3,CEurope fights inflation with rate hike
OL,4,Cafter Credit Suisse crisis amid fears
OL,5,Cof market meltdown
